<typeStatus box="[151,199,1837,1861]" pageId="21" pageNumber="494">type</typeStatus>
series for the latter species. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dietrich &amp; Zahniser" authorityYear="2019" box="[632,805,1836,1860]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Makilingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="494" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrifrons">
<emphasis box="[632,805,1836,1860]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="494">M. tenebrifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguishable by the distinct coloration of the head and by the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
